page.title: 17BIRDS IN GARSTANG
page.content:
This is a list of the birds we have seen in and around Garstang in June 1985.The most common of all the birds is the House Sparrow which has learnt to live on human settlements.The more common birds are in capital letters and the rarer birds in small letters.
SWIFT SWALLOW JACKDAW THRUSH SPARROW SEAGULL CROW STARLING PIGEON ROOK CHAFFINCH BLUE TIT ROBIN MAGPIE BLACKBIRD GREAT TIT HOUSE MARTIN PIED WAGTAIL
Kestrel Little owl Sparrow Hawk Heron Tawny owl Oyster catcher Dipper Red Shank Black Cap Lapwing Barn Owl King Fisher
A.Whiteside W.Bevan R.Dewhurst.
